SARASOTA — Several key players will be making their spring debuts as the Rays continue their exhibition-opening road tour today in Sarasota against the Orioles. The Rays seek their first win after losses to the Twins and Red Sox this past weekend in Fort Myers. Randy Arozarena, Yandy Diaz, Wander Franco, Brandon Lowe and Manuel Margot are in the lineup for the first time. For Arozarena and Franco, the game action will serve as preparation for the World Baseball Classic, for which they leave next week. Elvin Rodriguez, a non-roster invitee, will start for the Rays, with two of their top left-handed relievers scheduled for action. Here is the Rays lineup: And for the Orioles: • • • Sign up for the Rays Report weekly newsletter to get fresh perspectives on the Tampa Bay Rays and the rest of the majors from sports columnist John Romano. Never miss out on the latest with the Bucs, Rays, Lightning, Florida college sports and more. Follow our Tampa Bay Times sports team on Twitter and Facebook.